< SPECIAL EVENT >
Hip & Knee Surgery … what to expect before, during & after surgery


Tuesday, 4th June 2019
5:30pm to 7:30pm
Venue: Lakeview Private Hospital, 17-19 Solent Circuit, Norwest, NSW 2153

This special information evening is essential for anyone wanting to understand what to expect from joint surgery – whether it be as a result of something they’re facing themselves or that which a friend, family member or someone close to them may be facing.
Hosted and held by Lakeview Private Hospital, the evening will include presentations by a number of the leading orthopaedic surgeons in New South Wales.

There will also be an invaluable talk on Arthritis by Dr John Fox as well as a tour of the excellent Lakeview Private Rehabilitation including its superb hydrotherapy pool.

Space is limited and bookings are essential.






Presenters:


Dr John Fox
BE MBBS FRACS (Orth) FAOrthA
Dr Fox specialises in all aspects of knee surgery and arthroscopy: Sports related injuries, Arthroscopic ACL reconstruction, Complex ligament reconstruction, Knee replacement surgery; primary and revision, Hip replacement surgery; primary and revision

Dr Roger Brighton
MBBS FRACS(Ortho) FAOrthA
Dr Brighton has been practising in the NorthWest sector of Sydney for nearly 20 years and subspecialises in Hip and Knee Joint Replacement, Revision Surgery and Arthroscopic Knee Surgery, including ACL Reconstruction.

Dr Michael Stening
MBBS FRACS (Orth)
Dr Stening is an orthopaedic surgeon who specialises in hip and knee arthroplasty surgery. His areas of specialty include anterior minimally invasive hip replacement,

… PLUS




… a tour of:

Lakeview Private Rehabilitation
Lakeview Private’s state of the art rehabilitation facility provides orthopaedic and reconditioning inpatient and outpatient services with the very latest in equipment, as well as a hydrotherapy pool and spa plus the combined expertise of the best of medical professionals
